<br>
As most classes we do suffer from high resists though, even more so due to the fact that most of our songs have more than one component causing the mob to get more than one resist attempt.<br>
<br>
So, what can we do then. Well, I'm going to try and lump them into two different categories.<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> Snares/Slows
L20 Largo's Melodic Binding     Singing  AE      33% slow, -9 AC
L23 Selo's Consonant Chain      Singing  Target  33% slow, snare
L48 Selo's Chords of Cessation  String   AE      19% slow, 29/69 x 3 ticks
L51 Largo's Absonant Binding    Singing  Target  33% slow, snare, -17 AC, -47 Agi
L54 Selo's Assonait Strane      String   AE      24% slow, snare
L60 Angstlich's Assonance       Brass    Target  31% slow, 28/61 x 10 ticks
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->As you can see, all our snare songs have slows included. Don't worry, if better slow is on target it will overwrite, we can still snare it though.<br>
But this also means that if a target is immune to slow (I'm not talking highly resistant. Immune.) then a bard can't snare it, because the spell wont land on the mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
And vice versa, although we do have slow song without snares, but only the L60 one is target, the rest are AE.<br>
My favorite one of the bunch is the L51, Largo's Absonant Binding, thanks to the AC and Agi debuffs.<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> DoT/Resist debuffs
L30 Fufil's Curtaling Chant  Percussion       Target  21/50 dmg x 3 ticks, -15/36 MR
L38 Tuyen's Chant of Flame   Percussion       Target  31/74 dmg x 3 ticks, -15/36 FR
L46 Tuyen's Chant of Frost   Percussion       Target  31/74 dmg x 3 ticks, -15/36 CR
L55 Occlusion of Sound       Percussion(req)  Target  -23 MR/FR/CR. Unresistable!
L59 Denon's Bereavement      String           AE      30/71 dmg x 3 ticks, -15/35 MR
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->Who can argue with OoS? Only downer is that I have to equip a drum to sing it. Until I get my hands on the epic that is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Too bad Fufil's Curtaling Chant don't stack with OoS, or I would be singing that when we need to land slow. The other 'chants' stack fine with OoS though.<br>
L30, L38 and L46 is a very powerful solo tool too. Manafree 198 dmg per tick! 2/3 or 132 if you're kiting the mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, what's good and what's not?<br>
Well, what I usually sing in ToV if I'm the only bard there is,<br>
<br>
Always:<br>
* and always Elemental Chorus. An AE MR/FR/CR buff for 100 to all with my drum! Watch the AE damage drop <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
On incoming:<br>
* Occlusion of Sound. Hands down one of our best debuffs. This one stays up until slow has landed.<br>
<br>
After slow:<br>
If in MA group:<br>
* Battlecry of the Vah Shir. 15% haste that stacks with everything, and breaks the haste cap!<br>
* Cantata of Replenishment. HP/Mana/Stamina regen. Range is quite good so the cleric hiding behind the corner gets extra mana if we're lucky.<br>
If not in MA group:<br>
* same as in MA if lots of rogues, or I might do the set described next...<br>
<br>
Before/when 'NUKE' is called:<br>
* Occlusion of Sound. Hands down one of our best debuffs. This one stays up until slow has landed.<br>
* Either Tuyen's Chant of Flame or Frost depending on the wurm type. That means that FR/CR will be debuffed by 59, not including other debuffs.<br>
<br>
So, as you see, I got 3 different twists to do during different parts of the battle.<br>
On incoming, Chorus - OoS, repeat. I don't risk dropping OoS or Chorus here for a 3rd song.<br>
After slow, Chorus - Battlecry - Cantata. One may drop for a split second due to lag, but I can keep this up 99% of the time.<br>
Nuke-mode, Chorus - OoS - Chant<br>
<br>
<br>
PS. All the numbers quoted is what I would do today at L55 with the instruments I got ATM.<br>
